com.github.robtimus.validation.yearmonth

Annotation Type YearMonthNotAfter


  • @Documented
 @Constraint(validatedBy={})
 @YearMonthMinBefore(moment="",
                    duration="P0D")
 @ReportAsSingleViolation
 @Target(value={METHOD,FIELD,ANNOTATION_TYPE,CONSTRUCTOR,PARAMETER,TYPE_USE})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Repeatable(value=YearMonthNotAfter.List.class)
public @interface YearMonthNotAfter
    Validates that the year-month part of a date/time object is not after a specific moment in time. More specifically, for a date/time object object, validates that object.yearMonth <= moment.

    Supported types are:

    • Date
    • Calendar
    • Instant
    • LocalDate
    • LocalDateTime
    • OffsetDateTime
    • ZonedDateTime

    null elements are considered valid.

    Author:
    Rob Spoor

    • Element Detail

      • moment

        @OverridesAttribute(constraint=YearMonthMinBefore.class)
public abstract String moment
        The moment against which to validate. This should either be a value that can be parsed to YearMonth, or now to use the current moment in time as defined by the ClockProvider attached to the Validator or ValidatorFactory. The default ClockProvider defines the current time according to the virtual machine, applying the current default time zone if needed.

      • message

        public abstract String message
        The error message.
        Default:
        "{com.github.robtimus.validation.yearmonth.YearMonthNotAfter.message}"

      • groups

        public abstract Class<?>[] groups
        The validation groups.
        Default:

      • payload

        public abstract Class<? extends Payload>[] payload
        The payload.
        Default:

      • zoneId

        @OverridesAttribute(constraint=YearMonthMinBefore.class)
public abstract String zoneId
        The zone id to use. This should be system for the value returned by ZoneId.systemDefault(), provided for the zone id from the actual value, or otherwise a value that is accepted by ZoneId.of(String) for a specific zone id.
        • For Calendar, OffsetDateTime and ZonedDateTime, if the zone id is not provided, the value is converted to the given zone id before extracting the year-month.
        • For Date and Instant, no zone id is available, so provided is not allowed.
        • For LocalDate and LocalDateTime, no zone id is applicable, so only the default value (system) is allowed.
        Default:
        "system"
